definition.value: This is an AE which is a common, non-threatening rash in newborns.
This is an AE which is a superficial skin infection that causes brown, scaly skin patches.
This is an AE which is an infectious disease caused by certain types of human herpes viruses.
This is an AE which is a tan or dark skin discoloration.
This is an AE which describes anatomy with the appearance and hair follicles get buried in the oedema and resemble an orange peel.
This is an AE which is a disorder where hives (urticaria) or large red welts form on the skin after exposure to a cold stimulus.
This is an AE which is the physical urticarias where wheals are elicited via specific physical (mechanical, temperature, radiation) stimuli.

This is an AE which is a rare condition in which exposure to ultraviolet or UV radiation, or sometimes even visible light, induces a case of urticaria or hives that can appear in both covered and uncovered areas of the skin.
This is an AE which is the most common form of cutaneous mastocytosis.
This is an AE which is a rare form of physical urticaria in which hives develop on the skin after contact with water, regardless of its temperature.
This is an AE which is a kind of skin rash with red, raised, itchy bumps.
This is an AE which is a kind of skin rash with red, raised, itchy bumps.

This is an AE which is a physical urticaria caused by pressure applied to the skin, and is characterized by the development of swelling and pain that usually occurs 3 to 12 hours after local pressure has been applied.

This is an AE which is a non-life-threatening and potentially distressing skin condition that is triggered by sunlight and artificial UV exposure in a genetically susceptible person, particularly in temperate climates during the spring and early summer.
This is an AE which is a group of infectious diseases that include epidemic typhus, scrub typhus, and murine typhus.
This is an AE which is a widespread rash occurring on the outside of the body and usually occurring in children.
This is an AE which is a viral disease characterized by a painful skin rash with blisters in a localized area.
This is an AE which is a viral disease characterized by a painful skin rash with blisters in a localized area and is multi-dermatomal.
This is an AE which is defined as more than twenty skin lesions appearing outside either the primarily affected dermatome or dermatomes directly adjacent to it.
This is an AE which is a medical sign consisting of a characteristic form of facial rash.
This is an AE which is an infection caused by the rubella virus.
This is an AE which is an infectious disease caused by certain types of human herpes viruses.
This is an AE which can refer to both beneficial medical procedures (e.g. vaccination) as well as non-beneficial or harmful natural processes (e.g. infection or disease).
This is an AE which is a change of the human skin which affects its color, appearance, or texture and is septic.
This is an AE which is a skin disease marked by small and itchy rashes due to sweat trapped under the skin by clogged sweat gland ducts.
This is an AE which is a bacterial disease spread by ticks.
This is an AE which is a rash (small spots) on the mucous membranes.
This is an AE which is a rare severe adverse reaction to smallpox vaccination.
This is an AE which is a life-threatening condition  with herpes that arises when the body's response to infection causes injury to its own tissues and organs.
This is an AE which is a chronic autoimmune blistering skin condition, characterised by intensely itchy blisters filled with a watery fluid.

This is an AE which is a rare but severe disseminated infection that generally occurs at sites of skin damage produced by, for example, atopic dermatitis, burns, long-term usage of topical steroids or eczema.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the skin, typically characterized by itchiness, redness and a rash.
This is an AE which is a common type of pruritic dermatitis and  can also be known as xerosis, which is dry skin.
This is an AE which is a form of typhus transmitted by fleas (Xenopsylla cheopis), usually on rats, in contrast to epidemic typhus which is usually transmitted by lice.
This is an AE which is a clog of the eccrine sweat gland.
This is an AE which is an itchy eruption of the skin.
This is an AE which may mimic diseases that present with annular configuration and the differential diagnosis is broad.
This is an AE which is an infectious disease caused by the cowpox virus.
This is an AE which is a large, complex, enveloped virus belonging to the poxvirus family.
This is an AE which is a slow-growing (16- to 20-hour generation time) aerobic bacterium and the causative agent of tuberculosis in cattle (known as bovine TB).
This is an AE which is flat, hyperpigmented birthmarks.
This is an AE which is clusters of concentrated melaninized cells which are most easily visible on people with a fair complexion.
This is an AE which is a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly defined edge, surrounded by normal-appearing skin.
This is an AE which is a skin condition characterized by excessively dry skin.
This is an AE which is a skin condition characterized by excessively dry skin.
This is an AE which is a discoloration of the human skin caused by a vascular anomaly (a capillary malformation in the skin).
This is an AE which is a condition in which hair is lost from some or all areas of the body.
This is an AE which is a condition characterized by a skin eruption on the trunk and proximal extremities.
This is an AE which is redness of the skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries and it is epiglottic.
This is an AE which is a common type of conjunctival stromal degeneration in the eye.
